{"id":136,"date":"2015-08-03T13:58:53","date_gmt":"2015-08-03T11:58:53","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/smit.co.za\/?p=136"},"modified":"2022-05-12T20:54:58","modified_gmt":"2022-05-12T18:54:58","slug":"lyricsmeaning-za-net-revamped","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/lyricsmeaning-za-net-revamped\/","title":{"rendered":"Lyricsmeaning.za.net Revamped"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>I recently saw that my old Lyrics &amp; Meaning website (<a href=\"https:\/\/lyricsmeaning.za.net\">lyricsmeaning.za.net<\/a>) was attacked with lots of spam bots, and the lyrics were not updating properly etc, so I decided its time to revamp! Yes, it looks much much better:<\/p>\n<p><center><strong>Old vs New<\/strong><br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/oldscreenshot.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"old screenshot\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/oldscreenshot-300x272.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"272\" \/><\/a>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/newscreenshot.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-145\" alt=\"new screenshot\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/newscreenshot-300x207.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/newscreenshot-300x207.png 300w, https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/newscreenshot.png 990w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/center><br \/>\nFor the Front-End, I used:<\/p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Angular.JS<\/h2>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/pic_angular.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"angular\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/pic_angular.jpg\" width=\"135\" height=\"135\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>I chose Angular because I have never created a single page application before, and it should allow me to port to a hybrid mobile app easily when the time comes.\u00a0**Ok I know Angular 2 is coming out soon, but at the time I started the revamp there was only version 1. \u00a0The design uses Bootstrap, and uses basic REST calls to update the data via:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">ASP.NET Web API 2<\/h2>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/asp-net-web-api.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"asp-net-web-api\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/asp-net-web-api-300x121.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"121\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Not much to talk about here, its a normal REST service, which connects to a SQL Database, using Entity Framework (5), coded in C#. This REST service should allow other application to get lyrics from the database etc. I tried to remove some of the spam with server code as well.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/winamp_logo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-137 aligncenter\" alt=\"Winamp Logo\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/winamp_logo.png\" width=\"110\" height=\"110\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/winampscreenshot.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"winamps screenshot\" src=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/winampscreenshot-300x166.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"166\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>An ofcource, the lyricsmeaning app is still viewable in Winamp. For information on how to install, go to <a href=\"https:\/\/lyricsmeaning.za.net\">https:\/\/lyricsmeaning.za.net<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I recently saw that my old Lyrics &amp; Meaning website (lyricsmeaning.za.net) was attacked with lots of spam bots, and the lyrics were not updating properly etc, so I decided its time to revamp! Yes, it looks much much better: Old vs New \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 For the Front-End, I used: Angular.JS &nbsp; I&hellip; <a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/lyricsmeaning-za-net-revamped\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Lyricsmeaning.za.net Revamped<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":142,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/136"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=136"}],"version-history":[{"count":6,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/136\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":177,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/136\/revisions\/177"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/142"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=136"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=136"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/smit.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=136"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}